{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_9","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"for f in .ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/loops/001-foundation-domain-model-workspace-init-and-flow/20260311175055-spec.md .ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/loops/002-stage-contract-registry-and-deterministic/20260311183324-spec.md .ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/loops/003-workspace-governance-effective-config-and-active/20260311191151-spec.md; do printf 'FILE:%s\\\\n' \\\"\"'$f\"; sed -n '\"'1,220p' \\\"\"'$f\"; printf '\"'\\\\n'; done\"","aggregated_output":"FILE:.ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/loops/001-foundation-domain-model-workspace-init-and-flow/20260311175055-spec.md\n---\nartifact: spec\nloop: 1\nproject: ralph-burning-rewrite\nbackend: claude(opus)\nrole: planner\ncreated_at: 2026-03-11T17:50:55Z\n---\n\n# Feature: Foundation — Domain Model, Workspace Init, and Flow Discovery\n\n## Description\nBootstrap the `ralph-burning` Rust binary crate with the v1 domain model, workspace initialization, and flow discovery CLI commands. This is delivery roadmap slice 1: it establishes the Cargo project, bounded-context folder skeleton, core domain types, the `ralph-burning init` command that creates a `.ralph-burning/` workspace, and `flow list` / `flow show` commands that enumerate the four built-in flow presets with their stage sequences. It also seeds the conformance test harness with initial Gherkin scenario IDs covering workspace init and flow discovery.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `ralph-burning-rewrite/Cargo.toml` compiles a binary named `ralph-burning` (edition 2021, Rust stable)\n- [ ] Dependencies include at minimum: `clap` (derive), `serde`/`serde_json`, `toml`/`toml_edit`, `thiserror`, `chrono`, and `tokio` (rt-multi-thread)\n- [ ] Source tree contains the bounded-context folder skeleton: `src/contexts/{workspace_governance, project_run_record, workflow_composition, agent_execution, requirements_drafting, automation_runtime, conformance_spec}/mod.rs` plus `src/adapters/mod.rs` and `src/shared/mod.rs`\n- [ ] Domain model types defined in `src/shared/domain.rs` (or equivalent shared module): `FlowPreset` enum (`Standard`, `QuickDev`, `DocsChange`, `CiImprovement`), `StageId` enum with all stages from all four presets, `StageCursor` struct (stage, cycle, attempt, completion_round), `ProjectId`, `RunId`, `WorkspaceConfig` struct\n- [ ] Four built-in flow presets are defined in `src/contexts/workflow_composition/` with their exact stage sequences as specified in the master prompt section 9\n- [ ] `ralph-burning init` creates `.ralph-burning/workspace.toml` with sensible defaults (version field, created timestamp) and the required subdirectory stubs (`projects/`, `requirements/`, `daemon/tasks/`, `daemon/leases/`)\n- [ ] `ralph-burning init` on an already-initialized workspace prints an error message and exits non-zero (no implicit re-init)\n- [ ] `ralph-burning flow list` prints all four preset names with a short description\n- [ ] `ralph-burning flow show <flow-id>` prints the ordered stage list, validation profile defaults (final review enabled/disabled), and stage count for the given preset\n- [ ] `ralph-burning flow show` with an invalid flow-id exits non-zero with a clear error\n- [ ] CLI top-level uses `clap` subcommand routing with placeholder subcommand stubs for all v1 commands (config, project, run, requirements, daemon, conformance) that print \"not yet implemented\" and exit non-zero\n- [ ] `tests/conformance/features/workspace_init.feature` contains Gherkin scenarios: init fresh workspace, init already-initialized workspace, init verifies directory structure\n- [ ] `tests/conformance/features/flow_discovery.feature` contains Gherkin scenarios: list all presets, show each preset, show invalid preset\n- [ ] Unit tests exist for: flow preset stage ordering, stage cursor construction invariants (monotonic cycle/completion round), workspace config serialization round-trip\n- [ ] `cargo build` succeeds with no warnings; `cargo test` passes all tests\n- [ ] `cargo clippy` reports no warnings\n\n## Files to Modify/Create\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/Cargo.toml` — new crate manifest with binary target and dependencies\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/main.rs` — async entry point, tracing init, clap CLI dispatch\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/lib.rs` — public module re-exports\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/mod.rs` — top-level clap `Cli` struct with all subcommand groups (stubs for unimplemented ones)\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/init.rs` — `ralph-burning init` implementation\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/flow.rs` — `ralph-burning flow list` and `flow show` implementation\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/config.rs` — placeholder stub\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/project.rs` — placeholder stub\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/run.rs` — placeholder stub\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/requirements.rs` — placeholder stub\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/daemon.rs` — placeholder stub\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/conformance.rs` — placeholder stub\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/mod.rs` — shared module root\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs` — core domain types (FlowPreset, StageId, StageCursor, ProjectId, RunId, WorkspaceConfig)\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs` — shared error types using `thiserror`\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workspace_governance/mod.rs` — workspace init logic, config loading, workspace version check\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs` — flow preset registry, stage sequence definitions\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/mod.rs` — module stub\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/agent_execution/mod.rs` — module stub\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/requirements_drafting/mod.rs` — module stub\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/mod.rs` — module stub\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/mod.rs` — module stub\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/mod.rs` — adapter module stub\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs` — filesystem adapter for workspace creation (ports/adapters boundary)\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/workspace_init.feature` — Gherkin scenarios for init\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/flow_discovery.feature` — Gherkin scenarios for flow commands\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/domain_test.rs` — unit tests for domain types\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/flow_preset_test.rs` — unit tests for flow preset definitions\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/workspace_test.rs` — unit tests for workspace config serialization\n\n## Dependencies\n- Requires: none (first slice)\n- Blocks: slice 2 (flow preset definitions + stage contracts + renderer contracts), slice 3 (workspace governance effective config), slice 4 (project/run canonical store)\n\n---\n\nFILE:.ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/loops/002-stage-contract-registry-and-deterministic/20260311183324-spec.md\n---\nartifact: spec\nloop: 2\nproject: ralph-burning-rewrite\nbackend: codex(gpt-5.4-xhigh)\nrole: planner\ncreated_at: 2026-03-11T18:33:24Z\n---\n\nI’m reviewing `prompt.md`, the completed loop artifact, and recent git history to determine what’s already in place and what the next missing feature slice should be.\nI have the loop and commit boundaries. Next I’m reading the actual prompt/spec inputs and the rewrite code so I can separate shipped foundation work from the next missing slice.\nThe prompt lives under the existing orchestration workspace, not the rewrite tree. I’m pulling the project prompt plus loop spec and current implementation surface together now.\nThe checked-in crate is still a narrow foundation slice. I’m reading the workflow and workspace modules now to verify whether stage contracts, effective config, or any project/run persistence already slipped in before I plan the next feature.\nI’ve confirmed the current code matches the approved loop-1 foundation plus a later `flake.nix` addition. I’m checking the checkpoint diffs now so the next feature is anchored to what actually changed between planning, implementation, review, and current HEAD.\n# Feature: Stage Contract Registry and Deterministic Artifact Rendering\n\n## Description\nLoop 1 is complete: the approved artifact and git checkpoints `1dbe79b` through `60e6d0c` delivered the Rust crate skeleton, bounded-context module layout, workspace init, built-in flow discovery, and the shared `FlowPreset` / `StageId` foundation. The only later change at `cac0f25` adds `flake.nix` support and does not add workflow behavior. The next missing slice is the unfinished remainder of roadmap step 2: a `StageContract` and renderer layer for the already-defined stages. The current codebase has no stage payload schemas, no semantic validators, no failure-class mapping, and no deterministic Markdown artifact rendering, so later work on agent execution and `run start` would otherwise have no canonical contract to target.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Add a `StageContract` registry keyed by the existing `StageId`, and every stage already present in the four built-in presets resolves to exactly one contract without changing any approved flow IDs or stage ordering.\n- [ ] Introduce typed stage payload models plus JSON Schema generation/validation for all supported stages: `prompt_review`, `planning`, `implementation`, `qa`, `review`, `completion_panel`, `acceptance_qa`, `final_review`, `plan_and_implement`, `apply_fixes`, `docs_plan`, `docs_update`, `docs_validation`, `ci_plan`, `ci_update`, and `ci_validation`.\n- [ ] Planning-style contracts (`prompt_review`, `planning`, `docs_plan`, `ci_plan`) require structured problem framing, assumptions or open questions, ordered proposed work, and explicit readiness or risk fields.\n- [ ] Execution/update contracts (`implementation`, `plan_and_implement`, `apply_fixes`, `docs_update`, `ci_update`) require structured change summaries, intended or completed steps, validation evidence or plans, and outstanding-risk fields.\n- [ ] Validation/review contracts (`qa`, `docs_validation`, `ci_validation`, `acceptance_qa`, `review`, `final_review`, `completion_panel`) require an explicit outcome/decision enum plus evidence, findings or gaps, and follow-up or amendment data when the outcome is not cleanly approved.\n- [ ] Contract evaluation order is fixed: schema validation runs first, semantic validation runs only on schema-valid payloads, and rendering runs only on payloads that passed both prior steps.\n- [ ] Introduce the canonical failure-class enum needed by later slices, including `transport_failure`, `schema_validation_failure`, `domain_validation_failure`, `timeout`, `cancellation`, and `qa_review_outcome_failure`.\n- [ ] Stage contracts map non-passing QA/review/completion decisions to `qa_review_outcome_failure` without treating them as schema or domain failures.\n- [ ] State invariants for this slice are explicit: on schema failure, semantic validation and rendering do not run; on domain failure, rendering does not run; on any failure, no success bundle is returned; callers receive either `validated payload + rendered artifact` together or an error, never one without the other.\n- [ ] Markdown renderers are deterministic and stage-specific: the same validated payload always renders byte-identical output, uses canonical `cycle` terminology, and is derived only from validated structured fields rather than raw backend text.\n- [ ] Raw backend output remains diagnostic-only input to the contract evaluator and is kept separate from payload and artifact outputs so later persistence work can store diagnostics without using Markdown as protocol.\n- [ ] Add unit tests proving every stage in every built-in flow has contract coverage, schema failures short-circuit semantic validation, semantic failures short-circuit rendering, and repeated renders of the same payload are identical.\n- [ ] Add conformance scenario IDs for successful contract evaluation, schema failure, domain failure, and QA/review outcome failure so later `run start` work inherits fixed public expectations.\n- [ ] `cargo test` and `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings` pass after the contract and renderer modules are added.\n\n## Files to Modify/Create\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/Cargo.toml` - add schema/validation dependencies needed for typed JSON Schema support\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs` - add shared failure-class and artifact/contract identity types used across contracts\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs` - add explicit schema-validation, domain-validation, and renderer error variants\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs` - expose the stage-contract registry alongside the existing flow definitions\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs` - define `StageContract`, registry lookup, contract evaluation ordering, and failure mapping\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/payloads.rs` - define typed payload structs and schema metadata for each stage or contract family\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/renderers.rs` - implement deterministic Markdown renderers from validated payloads\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit.rs` - register new unit test modules\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/stage_contract_test.rs` - cover registry completeness, validation ordering, and failure-class behavior\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/renderer_test.rs` - cover deterministic rendering and artifact content shape\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/stage_contracts.feature` - add scenario IDs describing contract success and failure behavior\n\n## Dependencies\n- Requires: Loop 1 foundation — domain model, workspace init, and flow discovery\n- Blocks: agent execution facade with structured-output guarantee, standard preset `run start` vertical path, and later retry/remediation semantics\n\n---\n\nFILE:.ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/loops/003-workspace-governance-effective-config-and-active/20260311191151-spec.md\n---\nartifact: spec\nloop: 3\nproject: ralph-burning-rewrite\nbackend: claude(opus)\nrole: planner\ncreated_at: 2026-03-11T19:11:51Z\n---\n\nNow I have a complete picture of the project state. Let me analyze and produce the next feature spec.\n\n**Completed:**\n- Loop 1 (roadmap slice 1): Foundation — domain model, workspace init, flow discovery\n- Loop 2 (roadmap slice 2): Stage contract registry and deterministic artifact rendering\n\n**Next in roadmap:** Slice 3 — Workspace governance effective config + active project resolution\n\n# Feature: Workspace Governance Effective Config and Active Project Resolution\n\n## Description\nImplement roadmap slice 3: layered workspace configuration with `config show/get/set/edit` CLI commands, and active-project resolution via the `.ralph-burning/active-project` pointer file. The existing `workspace_governance` context currently handles workspace init and config loading but has no support for effective configuration (workspace-level defaults, runtime overrides), mutable config updates, or tracking which project is currently selected. This slice fills that gap so that downstream work (project/run canonical store in slice 4, agent execution in slice 5) can resolve effective settings and know which project commands target without explicit `--id` flags.\n\nThe config surface covers keys implied by the master prompt: `prompt_review.enabled` (controls whether the optional `prompt_review` stage runs in the `standard` flow), default backend family, default model overrides, and validation strictness. The implementation stores configuration in `workspace.toml` using a structured TOML schema, resolves effective values through a defaults-then-override chain, and enforces fail-fast on unsupported workspace versions (invariant already partially present, now wired through all config-reading paths).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `workspace.toml` schema is extended with an optional `[settings]` table supporting at minimum these keys: `prompt_review.enabled` (bool, default `true`), `default_flow` (string, must be a valid `FlowPreset`, default `\"standard\"`), `default_backend` (string, optional), `default_model` (string, optional). Unknown keys in `[settings]` are preserved on round-trip (forward-compatible editing).\n- [ ] An `EffectiveConfig` struct in `workspace_governance` resolves the full configuration by merging persisted `workspace.toml` settings with compiled defaults. Every supported key has a typed accessor with a documented default value. `EffectiveConfig::load(base_dir)` is the single entry point for all config reads.\n- [ ] `ralph-burning config show` loads the workspace, checks the version (fail-fast on mismatch), and prints all effective settings as a human-readable TOML-like table showing each key, its effective value, and its source (`default` or `workspace.toml`).\n- [ ] `ralph-burning config get <key>` prints the effective value for a single key. Exits non-zero with a clear error for unknown keys.\n- [ ] `ralph-burning config set <key> <value>` validates the key name and value type, writes the updated value into `workspace.toml` under `[settings]`, and prints a confirmation. Exits non-zero for invalid keys or values (e.g., setting `default_flow` to an unknown preset).\n- [ ] `ralph-burning config edit` opens `workspace.toml` in `$EDITOR` (or `$VISUAL`, falling back to `vi`). After the editor exits, the file is re-validated; if validation fails, the user is warned on stderr and the command exits non-zero (but the file is not reverted — the user must fix manually).\n- [ ] `active-project` is a plain-text file in `.ralph-burning/` containing a single project ID (trimmed, no newline normalization issues). When absent, commands that require an active project fail with an explicit message naming `project select`.\n- [ ] `ralph-burning project select <id>` validates that the project directory `.ralph-burning/projects/<id>/` exists and contains `project.toml`, writes the ID to `active-project`, and prints a confirmation. Exits non-zero if the project does not exist.\n- [ ] A `resolve_active_project(base_dir) -> AppResult<ProjectId>` function in `workspace_governance` reads and validates `active-project`, returning a typed `ProjectId` or a descriptive error. This function is the single resolution point for all commands that operate on the current project.\n- [ ] All config and active-project commands check workspace version first and fail fast on unsupported versions (wiring the existing `ensure_supported_workspace_version` through the CLI path).\n- [ ] The filesystem adapter (`adapters/fs.rs`) gains methods for atomic config writes (write-to-temp-then-rename) and active-project file read/write, keeping side effects behind the adapter boundary.\n- [ ] Unit tests cover: `EffectiveConfig` default resolution, override merging, round-trip serialization of extended `workspace.toml`, unknown-key preservation, invalid key/value rejection, active-project read/write/missing cases.\n- [ ] Integration tests cover: `config show` output format, `config get` known and unknown keys, `config set` valid and invalid mutations, `project select` with existing and non-existing project directories.\n- [ ] Gherkin scenarios added to `tests/conformance/features/workspace_config.feature`: show effective config, get known key, get unknown key, set valid key, set invalid value, set invalid key, edit with valid result, edit with invalid result.\n- [ ] Gherkin scenarios added to `tests/conformance/features/active_project.feature`: select existing project, select non-existing project, resolve when no active project set, resolve after valid select.\n- [ ] `cargo test` and `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings` pass after all changes.\n\n## Files to Modify/Create\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs` — extend `WorkspaceConfig` with optional `settings: WorkspaceSettings` field; add `WorkspaceSettings` struct with typed config fields and defaults\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs` — add error variants: `UnknownConfigKey`, `InvalidConfigValue`, `NoActiveProject`, `ProjectNotFound`, `EditorFailed`\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workspace_governance/mod.rs` — add `EffectiveConfig` struct with `load()`, `get()`, `set()` methods; add `resolve_active_project()` and `set_active_project()` functions; refactor config loading to use extended schema\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workspace_governance/config.rs` — (new) effective config resolution logic, key registry, default values, validation of key names and value types\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs` — add `write_atomic()`, `read_active_project()`, `write_active_project()`, `open_editor()` methods\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/config.rs` — implement `show`, `get`, `set`, `edit` handlers replacing the current stubs\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/project.rs` — implement `select` handler (other project subcommands remain stubs)\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/config_test.rs` — unit tests for effective config resolution, merging, serialization, key validation\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/active_project_test.rs` — unit tests for active-project read/write/missing\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/workspace_config.feature` — Gherkin scenarios for config commands\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/active_project.feature` — Gherkin scenarios for active project resolution\n\n## Dependencies\n- Requires: Loop 1 (workspace init, `WorkspaceConfig`, filesystem adapter) and Loop 2 (flow preset validation for `default_flow` config key)\n- Blocks: Slice 4 (project/run canonical store needs `resolve_active_project` and effective config), Slice 5 (agent execution needs default backend/model config resolution), Slice 6 (`run start` needs active project and effective config for prompt_review gate)\n\n---\n\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
